## V2 Apps [/v2/apps]

### appscreate [POST]
Create a new app by submitting an app specification. For documentation on app specifications (`AppSpec` objects), please refer to [the product documentation](https://docs.digitalocean.com/products/app-platform/reference/app-spec/).

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Accept:application/json


    + Attributes (V2 Apps Request)


    + Body

            {
                "spec": {
                    "name": "web-app",
                    "region": "nyc",
                    "services": [
                        {
                            "environment_slug": "node-js",
                            "github": {
                                "branch": "main",
                                "deploy_on_push": true,
                                "repo": "digitalocean/sample-golang"
                            },
                            "instance_count": 2,
                            "instance_size_slug": "basic-xxs",
                            "name": "api",
                            "routes": [
                                {
                                    "path": "/api"
                                }
                            ],
                            "run_command": "bin/api"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        A JSON or YAML of a `spec` object.

    + Attributes (V2 Apps Response1)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



