## V2 Apps Propose [/v2/apps/propose]

### appsvalidateappSpec [POST]
To propose and validate a spec for a new or existing app, send a POST request to the `/v2/apps/propose` endpoint. The request returns some information about the proposed app, including app cost and upgrade cost. If an existing app ID is specified, the app spec is treated as a proposed update to the existing app.

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (V2 Apps Propose Request)


    + Body

            {
                "app_id": "b6bdf840-2854-4f87-a36c-5f231c617c84",
                "spec": {
                    "name": "web-app",
                    "region": "nyc",
                    "services": [
                        {
                            "environment_slug": "node-js",
                            "github": {
                                "branch": "main",
                                "deploy_on_push": true,
                                "repo": "digitalocean/sample-golang"
                            },
                            "instance_count": 2,
                            "instance_size_slug": "basic-xxs",
                            "name": "api",
                            "routes": [
                                {
                                    "path": "/api"
                                }
                            ],
                            "run_command": "bin/api"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        A JSON object.

    + Attributes (V2 Apps Propose Response)


    + Body

            {"app_cost":5,"app_name_available":true,"app_tier_upgrade_cost":17,"existing_static_apps":"2","max_free_static_apps":"3","spec":{"name":"sample-golang","region":"ams","services":[{"environment_slug":"go","github":{"branch":"branch","repo":"digitalocean/sample-golang"},"http_port":8080,"instance_count":1,"instance_size_slug":"basic-xxs","name":"web","routes":[{"path":"/"}],"run_command":"bin/sample-golang"}]}}


+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


