# Group CDN Endpoints

Content hosted in DigitalOcean's object storage solution,
[Spaces](https://www.digitalocean.com/docs/spaces/overview/),
can optionally be served by our globally distributed Content Delivery
Network (CDN). By sending requests to `/v2/cdn/endpoints`, you can list,
create, or delete CDN Endpoints as well as purge cached content. To use a
custom subdomain to access the CDN Endpoint, provide the ID of a
DigitalOcean managed TLS certificate and the fully qualified domain name
for the custom subdomain.

## V2 Cdn Endpoints [/v2/cdn/endpoints{?per_page,page}]

### cdnlistendpoints [GET]
To list all of the CDN endpoints available on your account, send a GET request to `/v2/cdn/endpoints`.
+ Parameters
    + per_page (number, optional) -

        Number of items returned per page

        + Default: 20
        + Sample: 2
    + page (number, optional) -

        Which 'page' of paginated results to return.

        + Default: 1
        + Sample: 1

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        The result will be a JSON object with an `endpoints` key. This will be set to an array of endpoint objects, each of which will contain the standard CDN endpoint attributes.

    + Attributes (V2 Cdn Endpoints Response)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



## V2 Cdn Endpoints [/v2/cdn/endpoints]

### cdncreateendpoint [POST]
To create a new CDN endpoint, send a POST request to `/v2/cdn/endpoints`. The
origin attribute must be set to the fully qualified domain name (FQDN) of a
DigitalOcean Space. Optionally, the TTL may be configured by setting the `ttl`
attribute.

A custom subdomain may be configured by specifying the `custom_domain` and
`certificate_id` attributes.

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (Endpoint)


    + Body

            {
                "origin": "static-images.nyc3.digitaloceanspaces.com",
                "ttl": 3600
            }


+ Response 201 (application/json)

        The response will be a JSON object with an `endpoint` key. This will be set to an object containing the standard CDN endpoint attributes.

    + Attributes (V2 Cdn Endpoints Response1)


    + Body

            {"endpoint":{"created_at":"2018-07-19T15:04:16Z","endpoint":"static-images.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com","id":"19f06b6a-3ace-4315-b086-499a0e521b76","origin":"static-images.nyc3.digitaloceanspaces.com","ttl":3600}}


+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



