# Group Certificates

In order to perform SSL termination on load balancers, DigitalOcean offers
two types of [SSL certificate management](https://www.digitalocean.com/docs/accounts/security/#certificates):

* **Custom**: User-generated certificates may be uploaded to DigitalOcean
where they will be placed in a fully encrypted and isolated storage system.

* **Let's Encrypt**: Certificates may be automatically generated by
DigitalOcean utilizing an integration with Let's Encrypt, the free and
open certificate authority. These certificates will also be automatically
renewed as required.

## V2 Certificates [/v2/certificates{?per_page,page}]

### certificateslist [GET]
To list all of the certificates available on your account, send a GET request to `/v2/certificates`.
+ Parameters
    + per_page (number, optional) -

        Number of items returned per page

        + Default: 20
        + Sample: 2
    + page (number, optional) -

        Which 'page' of paginated results to return.

        + Default: 1
        + Sample: 1

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        The result will be a JSON object with a `certificates` key. This will be set to an array of certificate objects, each of which will contain the standard certificate attributes.

    + Attributes (V2 Certificates Response)


    + Body

            {"certificates":[{"created_at":"2017-02-08T16:02:37Z","dns_names":[""],"id":"892071a0-bb95-49bc-8021-3afd67a210bf","name":"web-cert-01","not_after":"2017-02-22T00:23:00Z","sha1_fingerprint":"dfcc9f57d86bf58e321c2c6c31c7a971be244ac7","state":"verified","type":"custom"},{"created_at":"2018-03-09T18:44:11Z","dns_names":["www.example.com","example.com"],"id":"ba9b9c18-6c59-46c2-99df-70da170a42ba","name":"web-cert-02","not_after":"2018-06-07T17:44:12Z","sha1_fingerprint":"479c82b5c63cb6d3e6fac4624d58a33b267e166c","state":"verified","type":"lets_encrypt"}],"links":{},"meta":{"total":2}}


+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



## V2 Certificates [/v2/certificates]

### certificatescreate [POST]
To upload new SSL certificate which you have previously generated, send a POST
request to `/v2/certificates`.

When uploading a user-generated certificate, the `private_key`,
`leaf_certificate`, and optionally the `certificate_chain` attributes should
be provided. The type must be set to `custom`.

When using Let's Encrypt to create a certificate, the `dns_names` attribute
must be provided, and the type must be set to `lets_encrypt`.

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (string)



+ Response 201 (application/json)

        The response will be a JSON object with a key called `certificate`. The value of this will be an object that contains the standard attributes associated with a certificate.
When using Let's Encrypt, the initial value of the certificate's `state` attribute will be `pending`. When the certificate has been successfully issued by Let's Encrypt, this will transition to `verified` and be ready for use.

    + Attributes (V2 Certificates Response1)


    + Body

            {"certificate":{"created_at":"2017-02-08T16:02:37Z","dns_names":[""],"id":"892071a0-bb95-49bc-8021-3afd67a210bf","name":"web-cert-01","not_after":"2017-02-22T00:23:00Z","sha1_fingerprint":"dfcc9f57d86bf58e321c2c6c31c7a971be244ac7","state":"verified","type":"custom"}}


