# Group Droplets

A [Droplet](https://www.digitalocean.com/docs/droplets/) is a DigitalOcean
virtual machine. By sending requests to the Droplet endpoint, you can
list, create, or delete Droplets.

Some of the attributes will have an object value. The `region` and `image`
objects will all contain the standard attributes of their associated
types. Find more information about each of these objects in their
respective sections.

## V2 Droplets [/v2/droplets{?tag_name}]

### dropletsdestroybyTag [DELETE]
To delete **all** Droplets assigned to a specific tag, include the `tag_name`
query parameter set to the name of the tag in your DELETE request. For
example,  `/v2/droplets?tag_name=$TAG_NAME`.

A successful request will receive a 204 status code with no body in response.
This indicates that the request was processed successfully.
+ Parameters
    + tag_name (string, required)

        Specifies Droplets to be deleted by tag.

        + Sample: env:test

+ Response 204 

        The action was successful and the response body is empty. This response has content-type set.




+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        The resource was not found.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"not_found","message":"The resource you requested could not be found."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



## V2 Droplets [/v2/droplets{?per_page,page,tag_name,name}]

### dropletslist [GET]
To list all Droplets in your account, send a GET request to `/v2/droplets`.

The response body will be a JSON object with a key of `droplets`. This will be
set to an array containing objects each representing a Droplet. These will
contain the standard Droplet attributes.

### Filtering Results by Tag

It's possible to request filtered results by including certain query parameters.
To only list Droplets assigned to a specific tag, include the `tag_name` query
parameter set to the name of the tag in your GET request. For example,
`/v2/droplets?tag_name=$TAG_NAME`.
+ Parameters
    + per_page (number, optional) -

        Number of items returned per page

        + Default: 20
        + Sample: 2
    + page (number, optional) -

        Which 'page' of paginated results to return.

        + Default: 1
        + Sample: 1
    + tag_name (string, optional)

        Used to filter Droplets by a specific tag. Can not be combined with `name`.

        + Sample: env:prod
    + name (string, optional)

        Used to filter list response by Droplet name returning only exact matches. It is case-insensitive and can not be combined with `tag_name`.

        + Sample: web-01

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        A JSON object with a key of `droplets`.

    + Attributes (V2 Droplets Response)


