# Group Floating IP Actions

As of 16 June 2022, we have renamed the Floating IP product to [Reserved IPs](https://docs.digitalocean.com/reference/api/api-reference/#tag/Reserved-IPs).
The Reserved IP product's endpoints function the exact same way as Floating IPs.
The only difference is the name change throughout the URLs and fields.
For example, the `floating_ips` field is now the `reserved_ips` field.
The Floating IP endpoints will remain active until fall 2023 before being
permanently deprecated.

With the exception of the [Projects API](https://docs.digitalocean.com/reference/api/api-reference/#tag/Projects),
we will reflect this change as an additional field in the responses across the API
where the `floating_ip` field is used. For example, the Droplet metadata response
will contain the field `reserved_ips` in addition to the `floating_ips` field.
Floating IPs retrieved using the Projects API will retain the original name.

Floating IP actions are commands that can be given to a DigitalOcean
floating IP. These requests are made on the actions endpoint of a specific
floating IP.

An action object is returned. These objects hold the current status of the
requested action.

## V2 Floating Ips Actions By Floating Ip [/v2/floating_ips/{floating_ip}/actions]

+ Parameters
    + floating_ip (string, required)

        A floating IP address.

        + Sample: 45.55.96.47

### floatingIPsActionlist [GET]
To retrieve all actions that have been executed on a floating IP, send a GET request to `/v2/floating_ips/$FLOATING_IP/actions`.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        The results will be returned as a JSON object with an `actions` key. This will be set to an array filled with action objects containing the standard floating IP action attributes.

    + Attributes (V2 Floating Ips Actions Response)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        The resource was not found.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"not_found","message":"The resource you requested could not be found."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}


### floatingIPsActionpost [POST]
To initiate an action on a floating IP send a POST request to
`/v2/floating_ips/$FLOATING_IP/actions`. In the JSON body to the request,
set the `type` attribute to on of the supported action types:

| Action     | Details
|------------|--------
| `assign`   | Assigns a floating IP to a Droplet
| `unassign` | Unassign a floating IP from a Droplet

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (string)



+ Response 201 (application/json)

        The response will be an object with a key called `action`. The value of this will be an object that contains the standard floating IP action attributes.

    + Attributes (V2 Floating Ips Actions Response1)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        The resource was not found.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"not_found","message":"The resource you requested could not be found."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



## V2 Floating Ips Actions By Floating Ip [/v2/floating_ips/{floating_ip}/actions/{action_id}]

+ Parameters
    + floating_ip (string, required)

        A floating IP address.

        + Sample: 45.55.96.47
    + action_id (number, required)

        A unique numeric ID that can be used to identify and reference an action.

        + Sample: 36804636

### floatingIPsActionget [GET]
To retrieve the status of a floating IP action, send a GET request to `/v2/floating_ips/$FLOATING_IP/actions/$ACTION_ID`.

