## V2 Monitoring Metrics Droplet Bandwidth [/v2/monitoring/metrics/droplet/bandwidth{?host_id,interface,direction,start,end}]

### monitoringgetdropletBandwidthMetrics [GET]
To retrieve bandwidth metrics for a given Droplet, send a GET request to `/v2/monitoring/metrics/droplet/bandwidth`. Use the `interface` query parameter to specify if the results should be for the `private` or `public` interface. Use the `direction` query parameter to specify if the results should be for `inbound` or `outbound` traffic.
+ Parameters
    + host_id (string, required)

        The droplet ID.

        + Sample: 17209102
    + interface (enum[string], required)

        The network interface.

        + Sample: private
        + Members
            + `private` 
            + `public` 

    + direction (enum[string], required)

        The traffic direction.

        + Sample: inbound
        + Members
            + `inbound` 
            + `outbound` 

    + start (string, required)

        Timestamp to start metric window.

        + Sample: 1620683817
    + end (string, required)

        Timestamp to end metric window.

        + Sample: 1620705417

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        The response will be a JSON object with a key called `data` and `status`.

    + Attributes (V2 Monitoring Metrics Droplet Bandwidth Response)


    + Body

            {"data":{"result":[{"metric":{"direction":"inbound","host_id":"222651441","interface":"private"},"values":[[1634052360,"0.016600450090265357"],[1634052480,"0.015085955677299055"],[1634052600,"0.014941163855322308"],[1634052720,"0.016214285714285712"]]}],"resultType":"matrix"},"status":"success"}


+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



