## V2 Projects By Project Id [/v2/projects/{project_id}]

+ Parameters
    + project_id (string, required)

        A unique identifier for a project.

        + Sample: 4de7ac8b-495b-4884-9a69-1050c6793cd6

### projectsdelete [DELETE]
To delete a project, send a DELETE request to `/v2/projects/$PROJECT_ID`. To
be deleted, a project must not have any resources assigned to it. Any existing
resources must first be reassigned or destroyed, or you will receive a 412 error.

A successful request will receive a 204 status code with no body in response.
This indicates that the request was processed successfully.

+ Response 204 

        The action was successful and the response body is empty.




+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        The resource was not found.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"not_found","message":"The resource you requested could not be found."}


+ Response 412 (application/json)

        Only an empty project can be deleted.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"precondition_failed","message":"cannot delete a project with resources. move or remove the resources first"}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

