            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}




# Group Snapshots

[Snapshots](https://www.digitalocean.com/docs/images/snapshots/) are saved
instances of a Droplet or a block storage volume, which is reflected in
the `resource_type` attribute. In order to avoid problems with compressing
filesystems, each defines a `min_disk_size` attribute which is the minimum
size of the Droplet or volume disk when creating a new resource from the
saved snapshot.

To interact with snapshots, you will generally send requests to the
snapshots endpoint at `/v2/snapshots`.

## V2 Snapshots [/v2/snapshots{?per_page,page,resource_type}]

### snapshotslist [GET]
To list all of the snapshots available on your account, send a GET request to
`/v2/snapshots`.

The response will be a JSON object with a key called `snapshots`. This will be
set to an array of `snapshot` objects, each of which will contain the standard
snapshot attributes.

### Filtering Results by Resource Type

It's possible to request filtered results by including certain query parameters.

#### List Droplet Snapshots

To retrieve only snapshots based on Droplets, include the `resource_type`
query parameter set to `droplet`. For example, `/v2/snapshots?resource_type=droplet`.

#### List Volume Snapshots

To retrieve only snapshots based on volumes, include the `resource_type`
query parameter set to `volume`. For example, `/v2/snapshots?resource_type=volume`.
+ Parameters
    + per_page (number, optional) -

        Number of items returned per page

        + Default: 20
        + Sample: 2
    + page (number, optional) -

        Which 'page' of paginated results to return.

        + Default: 1
        + Sample: 1
    + resource_type (enum[string], optional)

        Used to filter snapshots by a resource type.

        + Sample: droplet
        + Members
            + `droplet` 
            + `volume` 


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        A JSON object with a key of `snapshots`.

    + Attributes (V2 Snapshots Response)


    + Body

            {"links":{},"meta":{"total":2},"snapshots":[{"created_at":"2020-07-28T16:47:44Z","id":"6372321","min_disk_size":25,"name":"web-01-1595954862243","regions":["nyc3","sfo3"],"resource_id":"200776916","resource_type":"droplet","size_gigabytes":2.34,"tags":["web","env:prod"]},{"created_at":"2019-09-28T23:14:30Z","id":"fbe805e8-866b-11e6-96bf-000f53315a41","min_disk_size":2,"name":"pvc-01-1595954862243","regions":["nyc1"],"resource_id":"89bcc42f-85cf-11e6-a004-000f53315871","resource_type":"volume","size_gigabytes":0.1008,"tags":["k8s"]}]}


+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



## V2 Snapshots By Snapshot Id [/v2/snapshots/{snapshot_id}]

+ Parameters
    + snapshot_id (string, required)

        Either the ID of an existing snapshot. This will be an integer for a Droplet snapshot or a string for a volume snapshot.

        + Sample: 6372321

### snapshotsdelete [DELETE]
Both Droplet and volume snapshots are managed through the `/v2/snapshots/`
endpoint. To delete a snapshot, send a DELETE request to
`/v2/snapshots/$SNAPSHOT_ID`.

A status of 204 will be given. This indicates that the request was processed
successfully, but that no response body is needed.

+ Response 204 

        The action was successful and the response body is empty.




+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

