# Group Tags

A tag is a label that can be applied to a resource (currently Droplets,
Images, Volumes, Volume Snapshots, and Database clusters) in order to
better organize or facilitate the lookups and actions on it.

Tags have two attributes: a user defined `name` attribute and an embedded
`resources` attribute with information about resources that have been tagged.

## V2 Tags [/v2/tags{?per_page,page}]

### tagslist [GET]
To list all of your tags, you can send a GET request to `/v2/tags`.
+ Parameters
    + per_page (number, optional) -

        Number of items returned per page

        + Default: 20
        + Sample: 2
    + page (number, optional) -

        Which 'page' of paginated results to return.

        + Default: 1
        + Sample: 1

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        To list all of your tags, you can send a `GET` request to `/v2/tags`.

    + Attributes (V2 Tags Response)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



