# Group VPCs

[VPCs (virtual private clouds)](https://www.digitalocean.com/docs/networking/vpc/)
allow you to create virtual networks containing resources that can
communicate with each other in full isolation using private IP addresses.

By sending requests to the `/v2/vpcs` endpoint, you can create, configure,
list, and delete custom VPCs as well as retrieve information about the
resources assigned to them.

## V2 Vpcs [/v2/vpcs{?per_page,page}]

### vpcslist [GET]
To list all of the VPCs on your account, send a GET request to `/v2/vpcs`.
+ Parameters
    + per_page (number, optional) -

        Number of items returned per page

        + Default: 20
        + Sample: 2
    + page (number, optional) -

        Which 'page' of paginated results to return.

        + Default: 1
        + Sample: 1

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        The response will be a JSON object with a key called `vpcs`. This will be set to an array of objects, each of which will contain the standard attributes associated with a VPC

    + Attributes (V2 Vpcs Response)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        The resource was not found.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"not_found","message":"The resource you requested could not be found."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



## V2 Vpcs [/v2/vpcs]

### vpcscreate [POST]
To create a VPC, send a POST request to `/v2/vpcs` specifying the attributes
in the table below in the JSON body.

**Note:** If you do not currently have a VPC network in a specific datacenter
region, the first one that you create will be set as the default for that
region. The default VPC for a region cannot be changed or deleted.

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (V2 Vpcs Request)



+ Response 201 (application/json)

        The response will be a JSON object with a key called `vpc`. The value of this will be an object that contains the standard attributes associated with a VPC.

    + Attributes (V2 Vpcs Response1)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 429 (application/json)

        API Rate limit exceeded

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"too_many_requests","message":"API Rate limit exceeded."}


+ Response 500 (application/json)

        Server error.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"server_error","message":"Unexpected server-side error"}



## V2 Vpcs By Vpc Id [/v2/vpcs/{vpc_id}]

+ Parameters
    + vpc_id (string, required)

        A unique identifier for a VPC.

        + Sample: 4de7ac8b-495b-4884-9a69-1050c6793cd6

### vpcsdelete [DELETE]
To delete a VPC, send a DELETE request to `/v2/vpcs/$VPC_ID`. A 204 status
code with no body will be returned in response to a successful request.

The default VPC for a region can not be deleted. Additionally, a VPC can only
be deleted if it does not contain any member resources. Attempting to delete
a region's default VPC or a VPC that still has members will result in a
403 Forbidden error response.

+ Response 204 

        The action was successful and the response body is empty.




+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        The resource was not found.

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

