## V2 Vpcs Members By Vpc Id [/v2/vpcs/{vpc_id}/members{?resource_type,per_page,page}]

+ Parameters
    + vpc_id (string, required)

        A unique identifier for a VPC.

        + Sample: 4de7ac8b-495b-4884-9a69-1050c6793cd6

### vpcslistmembers [GET]
To list all of the resources that are members of a VPC, send a GET request to
`/v2/vpcs/$VPC_ID/members`.

To only list resources of a specific type that are members of the VPC,
included a `resource_type` query parameter. For example, to only list Droplets
in the VPC, send a GET request to `/v2/vpcs/$VPC_ID/members?resource_type=droplet`.
+ Parameters
    + resource_type (string, optional)

        Used to filter VPC members by a resource type.

        + Sample: droplet
    + per_page (number, optional) -

        Number of items returned per page

        + Default: 20
        + Sample: 2
    + page (number, optional) -

        Which 'page' of paginated results to return.

        + Default: 1
        + Sample: 1

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        The response will be a JSON object with a key called members. This will be set to an array of objects, each of which will contain the standard attributes associated with a VPC member.

    + Attributes (V2 Vpcs Members Response)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Unauthorized

    + Attributes (V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1)


    + Body

            {"id":"unauthorized","message":"Unable to authenticate you."}


