# Data Structures

## V2 1 Clicks Response (object)


### Properties
+ `1_clicks` (array[1Click], optional) 


## 1Click (object)


### Properties
+ `slug`: `monitoring` (string, required) - The slug identifier for the 1-Click application.
+ `type`: `kubernetes` (string, required) - The type of the 1-Click application.


## V2 1 Clicks 401 Error1 (object)


### Properties
+ `id`: `not_found` (string, required) - A short identifier corresponding to the HTTP status code returned. For  example, the ID for a response returning a 404 status code would be "not_found."
+ `message`: `The resource you were accessing could not be found.` (string, required) - A message providing additional information about the error, including  details to help resolve it when possible.
+ `request_id`: `4d9d8375-3c56-4925-a3e7-eb137fed17e9` (string, optional) - Optionally, some endpoints may include a request ID that should be  provided when reporting bugs or opening support tickets to help  identify the issue.


## V2 1 Clicks Kubernetes Request (object)


### Properties
+ `addon_slugs`: `["kube-state-metrics","loki"]` (array[string], required) - An array of 1-Click Application slugs to be installed to the Kubernetes cluster.
+ `cluster_uuid`: `50a994b6-c303-438f-9495-7e896cfe6b08` (string, required) - A unique ID for the Kubernetes cluster to which the 1-Click Applications will be installed.


## V2 1 Clicks Kubernetes Response (object)


### Properties
+ `message`: `Successfully kicked off addon job.` (string, optional) - A message about the result of the request.


## V2 Account Response (object)


### Properties
+ `account` (Account, optional) 


## Account (object)


### Properties
+ `droplet_limit`: `25` (number, required) - The total number of Droplets current user or team may have active at one time.
+ `email`: `sammy@digitalocean.com` (string, required) - The email address used by the current user to register for DigitalOcean.
+ `email_verified`: `true` (boolean, required) - If true, the user has verified their account via email. False otherwise.
+ `floating_ip_limit`: `5` (number, required) - The total number of Floating IPs the current user or team may have.
+ `status` (enum[string], required) - This value is one of "active", "warning" or "locked".
    + `active`
    + `warning`
    + `locked`
+ `status_message` (string, required) - A human-readable message giving more details about the status of the account.
+ `team` (Team, optional) - When authorized in a team context, includes information about the current team.
+ `uuid`: `b6fr89dbf6d9156cace5f3c78dc9851d957381ef` (string, required) - The unique universal identifier for the current user.


## Team (object)
When authorized in a team context, includes information about the current team.

### Properties
+ `name`: `My Team` (string, optional) - The name for the current team.
+ `uuid`: `5df3e3004a17e242b7c20ca6c9fc25b701a47ece` (string, optional) - The unique universal identifier for the current team.


## V2 Account Keys Response (object)


### Properties
+ `ssh_keys` (array[SshKey], optional) 
+ `links` (Links, optional) 
+ `meta` (Meta, required) 


## SshKey (object)


### Properties
+ `fingerprint`: `3b:16:bf:e4:8b:00:8b:b8:59:8c:a9:d3:f0:19:45:fa` (string, optional) - A unique identifier that differentiates this key from other keys using  a format that SSH recognizes. The fingerprint is created when the key is added to your account.
+ `id`: `512189` (number, optional) - A unique identification number for this key. Can be used to embed a  specific SSH key into a Droplet.
+ `name`: `My SSH Public Key` (string, required) - A human-readable display name for this key, used to easily identify the SSH keys when they are displayed.
+ `public_key`: `ssh-rsa AEXAMPLEaC1yc2EAAAADAQABAAAAQQDDHr/jh2Jy4yALcK4JyWbVkPRaWmhck3IgCoeOO3z1e2dBowLh64QAM+Qb72pxekALga2oi4GvT+TlWNhzPH4V example` (string, required) - The entire public key string that was uploaded. Embedded into the root user's `authorized_keys` file if you include this key during Droplet creation.


## Links (object)


### Properties
+ `pages`: `{"pages":{"first":"https://api.digitalocean.com/v2/account/keys?page=1","prev":"https://api.digitalocean.com/v2/account/keys?page=2"}}` (string, optional) 


## Pages (object)


### Properties
+ `last`: `https://api.digitalocean.com/v2/images?page=2` (string, optional) - URI of the last page of the results.
+ `next`: `https://api.digitalocean.com/v2/images?page=2` (string, optional) - URI of the next page of the results.


## Pages1 (object)


### Properties
+ `first`: `https://api.digitalocean.com/v2/images?page=1` (string, optional) - URI of the first page of the results.
+ `prev`: `https://api.digitalocean.com/v2/images?page=1` (string, optional) - URI of the previous page of the results.


## Meta (object)


### Properties
+ `total`: `1` (number, required) - Number of objects returned by the request.


## V2 Account Keys Response1 (object)


### Properties
+ `ssh_key` (SshKey, optional) 


## V2 Account Keys Request (object)


### Properties
+ `name`: `My SSH Public Key` (string, optional) - A human-readable display name for this key, used to easily identify the SSH keys when they are displayed.


## V2 Actions Response (object)


### Properties
+ `actions` (array[Action], optional) 
+ `links` (Links, optional) 
+ `meta` (Meta, required) 


## Action (object)


### Properties
+ `completed_at`: `2020-11-14T16:30:06Z` (string, optional, nullable) - A time value given in ISO8601 combined date and time format that represents when the action was completed.
+ `id`: `36804636` (number, optional) - A unique numeric ID that can be used to identify and reference an action.
+ `region` (Region, optional) 
+ `region_slug` (string, optional, nullable) 
+ `resource_id`: `3164444` (number, optional, nullable) - A unique identifier for the resource that the action is associated with.
+ `resource_type`: `droplet` (string, optional) - The type of resource that the action is associated with.
+ `started_at`: `2020-11-14T16:29:21Z` (string, optional) - A time value given in ISO8601 combined date and time format that represents when the action was initiated.
+ `status` (enum[string], optional) - The current status of the action. This can be "in-progress", "completed", or "errored".
    + `in-progress`
    + `completed`
    + `errored`
+ `type`: `create` (string, optional) - This is the type of action that the object represents. For example, this could be "transfer" to represent the state of an image transfer action.


## Region (object)


### Properties
+ `available`: `true` (boolean, required) - This is a boolean value that represents whether new Droplets can be created in this region.
+ `features`: `["private_networking","backups","ipv6","metadata","install_agent","storage","image_transfer"]` (array[string], required) - This attribute is set to an array which contains features available in this region
+ `name`: `New York 3` (string, required) - The display name of the region.  This will be a full name that is used in the control panel and other interfaces.
+ `sizes`: `["s-1vcpu-1gb","s-1vcpu-2gb","s-1vcpu-3gb","s-2vcpu-2gb","s-3vcpu-1gb","s-2vcpu-4gb","s-4vcpu-8gb","s-6vcpu-16gb","s-8vcpu-32gb","s-12vcpu-48gb","s-16vcpu-64gb","s-20vcpu-96gb","s-24vcpu-128gb","s-32vcpu-192g"]` (array[string], required) - This attribute is set to an array which contains the identifying slugs for the sizes available in this region.
+ `slug`: `nyc3` (string, required) - A human-readable string that is used as a unique identifier for each region.


## V2 Actions Response1 (object)


### Properties
+ `action` (Action, optional) 


## V2 Apps Response (object)


### Properties
+ `apps` (array[A list of app], optional) 
+ `links` (Links, optional) 
+ `meta` (Meta, required) 


