## AppSpec (object)
The desired configuration of an application.

### Properties
+ `databases` (array[Database], optional)

    Database instances which can provide persistence to workloads within the
    application.

+ `domains` (array[Domain], optional) - A set of hostnames where the application will be available.
+ `functions` (array[Function], optional) - Workloads which expose publicly-accessible HTTP services via Functions Components.
+ `jobs` (array[Job], optional) - Pre and post deployment workloads which do not expose publicly-accessible HTTP routes.
+ `name`: `web-app-01` (string, required) - The name of the app. Must be unique across all apps in the same account.
+ `region` (enum[string], optional) - The slug form of the geographical origin of the app. Default: `nearest available`
    + `ams`
    + `nyc`
    + `fra`
    + `sfo`
    + `sgp`
    + `blr`
    + `tor`
    + `lon`
    + `syd`
+ `services` (array[Service], optional) - Workloads which expose publicly-accessible HTTP services.
+ `static_sites` (array[StaticSite], optional) - Content which can be rendered to static web assets.
+ `workers` (array[Worker], optional) - Workloads which do not expose publicly-accessible HTTP services.


## Database (object)


### Properties
+ `cluster_name`: `cluster_name` (string, optional) - The name of the underlying DigitalOcean DBaaS cluster. This is required for production databases. For dev databases, if cluster_name is not set, a new cluster will be provisioned.
+ `db_name`: `my_db` (string, optional) - The name of the MySQL or PostgreSQL database to configure.
+ `db_user`: `superuser` (string, optional) - The name of the MySQL or PostgreSQL user to configure.
+ `engine` (enum[string], optional)

    - MYSQL: MySQL
    - PG: PostgreSQL
    - REDIS: Redis

    + `UNSET`
    + `MYSQL`
    + `PG`
    + `REDIS`
+ `name`: `prod-db` (string, required) - The name. Must be unique across all components within the same app.
+ `production`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Whether this is a production or dev database.
+ `version`: `12` (string, optional) - The version of the database engine


## Domain (object)


### Properties
+ `domain`: `app.example.com` (string, required) - The hostname for the domain
+ `minimum_tls_version` (enum[string], optional) - The minimum version of TLS a client application can use to access resources for the domain.  Must be one of the following values wrapped within quotations: `"1.2"` or `"1.3"`.
    + `1.2`
    + `1.3`
+ `type` (enum[string], optional)

    - DEFAULT: The default `.ondigitalocean.app` domain assigned to this app
    - PRIMARY: The primary domain for this app that is displayed as the default in the control panel, used in bindable environment variables, and any other places that reference an app's live URL. Only one domain may be set as primary.
    - ALIAS: A non-primary domain

    + `UNSPECIFIED`
    + `DEFAULT`
    + `PRIMARY`
    + `ALIAS`
+ `wildcard`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Indicates whether the domain includes all sub-domains, in addition to the given domain
+ `zone`: `example.com` (string, optional)

    Optional. If the domain uses DigitalOcean DNS and you would like App
    Platform to automatically manage it for you, set this to the name of the
    domain on your account.
    
    For example, If the domain you are adding is `app.domain.com`, the zone
    could be `domain.com`.



