## Cors (object)


### Properties
+ `allow_credentials`: `false` (boolean, optional) - Whether browsers should expose the response to the client-side JavaScript code when the request’s credentials mode is include. This configures the `Access-Control-Allow-Credentials` header.
+ `allow_headers`: `["Content-Type","X-Custom-Header"]` (array[string], optional) - The set of allowed HTTP request headers. This configures the `Access-Control-Allow-Headers` header.
+ `allow_methods`: `["GET","OPTIONS","POST","PUT","PATCH","DELETE"]` (array[string], optional) - The set of allowed HTTP methods. This configures the `Access-Control-Allow-Methods` header.
+ `allow_origins` (array[AllowOrigin], optional) - The set of allowed CORS origins.
+ `expose_headers`: `["Content-Encoding","X-Custom-Header"]` (array[string], optional) - The set of HTTP response headers that browsers are allowed to access. This configures the `Access-Control-Expose-Headers` header.
+ `max_age`: `5h30m` (string, optional) - An optional duration specifying how long browsers can cache the results of a preflight request. This configures the `Access-Control-Max-Age` header.


## AllowOrigin (object)


### Properties
+ `exact`: `https://www.example.com` (string, optional) - Exact string match. Only 1 of `exact`, `prefix`, or `regex` must be set.
+ `prefix`: `https://www.example.com` (string, optional) - Prefix-based match. Only 1 of `exact`, `prefix`, or `regex` must be set.
+ `regex`: `^.*example.com` (string, optional) - RE2 style regex-based match. Only 1 of `exact`, `prefix`, or `regex` must be set. For more information about RE2 syntax, see: https://github.com/google/re2/wiki/Syntax


