## HealthCheck (object)


### Properties
+ `failure_threshold`: `2` (number, optional) - The number of failed health checks before considered unhealthy.
+ `http_path`: `/health` (string, optional) - The route path used for the HTTP health check ping. If not set, the HTTP health check will be disabled and a TCP health check used instead.
+ `initial_delay_seconds`: `30` (number, optional) - The number of seconds to wait before beginning health checks.
+ `period_seconds`: `60` (number, optional) - The number of seconds to wait between health checks.
+ `port`: `80` (number, optional) - The port on which the health check will be performed. If not set, the health check will be performed on the component's http_port.
+ `success_threshold`: `3` (number, optional) - The number of successful health checks before considered healthy.
+ `timeout_seconds`: `45` (number, optional) - The number of seconds after which the check times out.


