Bandwidth usage for an app.

### Properties
+ `app_id`: `4f6c71e2-1e90-4762-9fee-6cc4a0a9f2cf` (string, optional) - The ID of the app.
+ `bandwidth_bytes`: `513668` (string, optional) - The used bandwidth amount in bytes.


## V2 Apps Propose Request (object)


### Properties
+ `app_id`: `b6bdf840-2854-4f87-a36c-5f231c617c84` (string, optional) - An optional ID of an existing app. If set, the spec will be treated as a proposed update to the specified app. The existing app is not modified using this method.
+ `spec` (AppSpec, required) - The desired configuration of an application.


## V2 Apps Propose Response (object)


### Properties
+ `app_cost`: `5` (number, optional) - The monthly cost of the proposed app in USD using the next pricing plan tier. For example, if you propose an app that uses the Basic tier, the `app_tier_upgrade_cost` field displays the monthly cost of the app if it were to use the Professional tier. If the proposed app already uses the most expensive tier, the field is empty.
+ `app_is_static`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Indicates whether the app is a static app.
+ `app_name_available`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Indicates whether the app name is available.
+ `app_name_suggestion`: `newName` (string, optional) - The suggested name if the proposed app name is unavailable.
+ `app_tier_downgrade_cost`: `17` (number, optional) - The monthly cost of the proposed app in USD using the previous pricing plan tier. For example, if you propose an app that uses the Professional tier, the `app_tier_downgrade_cost` field displays the monthly cost of the app if it were to use the Basic tier. If the proposed app already uses the lest expensive tier, the field is empty.
+ `existing_static_apps`: `2` (string, optional) - The maximum number of free static apps the account can have. We will charge you for any additional static apps.
+ `spec` (AppSpec, optional) - The desired configuration of an application.


