## Certificate (object)


### Properties
+ `created_at`: `2017-02-08T16:02:37Z` (string, optional) - A time value given in ISO8601 combined date and time format that represents when the certificate was created.
+ `dns_names`: `["www.example.com","example.com"]` (array[string], optional) - An array of fully qualified domain names (FQDNs) for which the certificate was issued.
+ `id`: `892071a0-bb95-49bc-8021-3afd67a210bf` (string, optional) - A unique ID that can be used to identify and reference a certificate.
+ `name`: `web-cert-01` (string, optional) - A unique human-readable name referring to a certificate.
+ `not_after`: `2017-02-22T00:23:00Z` (string, optional) - A time value given in ISO8601 combined date and time format that represents the certificate's expiration date.
+ `sha1_fingerprint`: `dfcc9f57d86bf58e321c2c6c31c7a971be244ac7` (string, optional) - A unique identifier generated from the SHA-1 fingerprint of the certificate.
+ `state` (enum[string], optional) - A string representing the current state of the certificate. It may be `pending`, `verified`, or `error`.
    + `pending`
    + `verified`
    + `error`
+ `type` (enum[string], optional) - A string representing the type of the certificate. The value will be `custom` for a user-uploaded certificate or `lets_encrypt` for one automatically generated with Let's Encrypt.
    + `custom`
    + `lets_encrypt`


## Lets Encrypt Certificate Request (object)


### Properties
+ `name`: `web-cert-01` (string, required) - A unique human-readable name referring to a certificate.
+ `type` (enum[string], optional) - A string representing the type of the certificate. The value will be `custom` for a user-uploaded certificate or `lets_encrypt` for one automatically generated with Let's Encrypt.
    + `custom`
    + `lets_encrypt`
+ `dns_names`: `["www.example.com","example.com"]` (array[string], required) - An array of fully qualified domain names (FQDNs) for which the certificate was issued. A certificate covering all subdomains can be issued using a wildcard (e.g. `*.example.com`).


