## InvoicePreview (object)
The invoice preview.

### Properties
+ `amount`: `23.45` (string, optional) - Total amount of the invoice, in USD.  This will reflect month-to-date usage in the invoice preview.
+ `invoice_period`: `2020-01` (string, optional) - Billing period of usage for which the invoice is issued, in `YYYY-MM`  format.
+ `invoice_uuid`: `fdabb512-6faf-443c-ba2e-665452332a9e` (string, optional) - The UUID of the invoice. The canonical reference for the invoice.
+ `updated_at`: `2020-01-23T06:31:50Z` (string, optional) - Time the invoice was last updated.  This is only included with the invoice preview.


## V2 Customers My Invoices Response1 (object)


### Properties
+ `invoice_items` (array[InvoiceItem], optional) 
+ `links` (Links, optional) 
+ `meta` (Meta, required) 


## InvoiceItem (object)


### Properties
+ `amount`: `12.34` (string, optional) - Billed amount of this invoice item. Billed in USD.
+ `description`: `a56e086a317d8410c8b4cfd1f4dc9f82` (string, optional) - Description of the invoice item.
+ `duration`: `744` (string, optional) - Duration of time this invoice item was used and subsequently billed.
+ `duration_unit`: `Hours` (string, optional) - Unit of time for duration.
+ `end_time`: `2020-02-01T00:00:00Z` (string, optional) - Time the invoice item stopped being billed for usage.
+ `group_description`: `my-doks-cluster` (string, optional) - Description of the invoice item when it is a grouped set of usage, such  as DOKS or databases.
+ `product`: `Kubernetes Clusters` (string, optional) - Name of the product being billed in the invoice item.
+ `project_name`: `web` (string, optional) - Name of the DigitalOcean Project this resource belongs to.
+ `resource_id`: `2353624` (string, optional) - ID of the resource billing in the invoice item if available.
+ `resource_uuid`: `711157cb-37c8-4817-b371-44fa3504a39c` (string, optional) - UUID of the resource billing in the invoice item if available.
+ `start_time`: `2020-01-01T00:00:00Z` (string, optional) - Time the invoice item began to be billed for usage.


