## V2 Databases Response (object)


### Properties
+ `databases` (array[Database1], optional) 


## Database1 (object)


### Properties
+ `connection` (Connection, optional) 
+ `created_at`: `2019-01-11T18:37:36Z` (string, optional) - A time value given in ISO8601 combined date and time format that represents when the database cluster was created.
+ `db_names`: `["doadmin"]` (array[string], optional, nullable) - An array of strings containing the names of databases created in the database cluster.
+ `engine` (enum[string], required) - A slug representing the database engine used for the cluster. The possible values are: "pg" for PostgreSQL, "mysql" for MySQL, "redis" for Redis, and "mongodb" for MongoDB.
    + `pg`
    + `mysql`
    + `redis`
    + `mongodb`
+ `id`: `9cc10173-e9ea-4176-9dbc-a4cee4c4ff30` (string, optional) - A unique ID that can be used to identify and reference a database cluster.
+ `maintenance_window` (MaintenanceWindow, optional, nullable) 
+ `name`: `backend` (string, required) - A unique, human-readable name referring to a database cluster.
+ `num_nodes`: `2` (number, required) - The number of nodes in the database cluster.
+ `private_connection` (PrivateConnection, optional) 
+ `private_network_uuid`: `d455e75d-4858-4eec-8c95-da2f0a5f93a7` (string, optional) - A string specifying the UUID of the VPC to which the database cluster will be assigned. If excluded, the cluster when creating a new database cluster, it will be assigned to your account's default VPC for the region.
+ `project_id`: `9cc10173-e9ea-4176-9dbc-a4cee4c4ff30` (string, optional) - The ID of the project that the database cluster is assigned to. If excluded when creating a new database cluster, it will be assigned to your default project.
+ `region`: `nyc3` (string, required) - The slug identifier for the region where the database cluster is located.
+ `rules` (array[Rule1], optional) 
+ `size`: `db-s-2vcpu-4gb` (string, required) - The slug identifier representing the size of the nodes in the database cluster.
+ `status` (enum[string], optional) - A string representing the current status of the database cluster.
    + `creating`
    + `online`
    + `resizing`
    + `migrating`
    + `forking`
+ `tags`: `["production"]` (array[string], optional, nullable) - An array of tags that have been applied to the database cluster.
+ `users` (array[User], optional, nullable) 
+ `version`: `10` (string, optional) - A string representing the version of the database engine in use for the cluster.
+ `version_end_of_availability`: `2023-05-09T00:00:00Z` (string, optional) - A timestamp referring to the date when the particular version will no longer be available for creating new clusters. If null, the version does not have an end of availability timeline.
+ `version_end_of_life`: `2023-11-09T00:00:00Z` (string, optional) - A timestamp referring to the date when the particular version will no longer be supported. If null, the version does not have an end of life timeline.


## Connection (object)


### Properties
+ `database`: `defaultdb` (string, optional) - The name of the default database.
+ `host`: `backend-do-user-19081923-0.db.ondigitalocean.com` (string, optional) - The FQDN pointing to the database cluster's current primary node.
+ `password`: `wv78n3zpz42xezdk` (string, optional) - The randomly generated password for the default user.
+ `port`: `25060` (number, optional) - The port on which the database cluster is listening.
+ `ssl`: `true` (boolean, optional) - A boolean value indicating if the connection should be made over SSL.
+ `uri`: `postgres://doadmin:wv78n3zpz42xezdk@backend-do-user-19081923-0.db.ondigitalocean.com:25060/defaultdb?sslmode=require` (string, optional) - A connection string in the format accepted by the `psql` command. This is provided as a convenience and should be able to be constructed by the other attributes.
+ `user`: `doadmin` (string, optional) - The default user for the database.


## MaintenanceWindow (object)


### Properties
+ `day`: `tuesday` (string, required) - The day of the week on which to apply maintenance updates.
+ `description`: `["Update TimescaleDB to version 1.2.1","Upgrade to PostgreSQL 11.2 and 10.7 bugfix releases"]` (array[string], optional) - A list of strings, each containing information about a pending maintenance update.
+ `hour`: `14:00` (string, required) - The hour in UTC at which maintenance updates will be applied in 24 hour format.
+ `pending`: `true` (boolean, optional) - A boolean value indicating whether any maintenance is scheduled to be performed in the next window.


## PrivateConnection (object)


### Properties
+ `database`: `defaultdb` (string, optional) - The name of the default database.
+ `host`: `backend-do-user-19081923-0.db.ondigitalocean.com` (string, optional) - The FQDN pointing to the database cluster's current primary node.
+ `password`: `wv78n3zpz42xezdk` (string, optional) - The randomly generated password for the default user.
+ `port`: `25060` (number, optional) - The port on which the database cluster is listening.
+ `ssl`: `true` (boolean, optional) - A boolean value indicating if the connection should be made over SSL.
+ `uri`: `postgres://doadmin:wv78n3zpz42xezdk@backend-do-user-19081923-0.db.ondigitalocean.com:25060/defaultdb?sslmode=require` (string, optional) - A connection string in the format accepted by the `psql` command. This is provided as a convenience and should be able to be constructed by the other attributes.
+ `user`: `doadmin` (string, optional) - The default user for the database.


## Rule1 (object)


### Properties
+ `cluster_uuid`: `9cc10173-e9ea-4176-9dbc-a4cee4c4ff30` (string, optional) - A unique ID for the database cluster to which the rule is applied.
+ `created_at`: `2019-01-11T18:37:36Z` (string, optional) - A time value given in ISO8601 combined date and time format that represents when the firewall rule was created.
+ `type` (enum[string], required) - The type of resource that the firewall rule allows to access the database cluster.
    + `droplet`
    + `k8s`
    + `ip_addr`
    + `tag`
    + `app`
+ `uuid`: `79f26d28-ea8a-41f2-8ad8-8cfcdd020095` (string, optional) - A unique ID for the firewall rule itself.
+ `value`: `ff2a6c52-5a44-4b63-b99c-0e98e7a63d61` (string, required) - The ID of the specific resource, the name of a tag applied to a group of resources, or the IP address that the firewall rule allows to access the database cluster.


## User (object)


### Properties
+ `mysql_settings` (MysqlSettings, optional) 
+ `name`: `app-01` (string, required) - The name of a database user.
+ `password`: `jge5lfxtzhx42iff` (string, optional) - A randomly generated password for the database user.
+ `role` (enum[string], optional)

    A string representing the database user's role. The value will be either
    "primary" or "normal".

    + `primary`
    + `normal`


## MysqlSettings (object)


### Properties
+ `auth_plugin` (enum[string], required)

    A string specifying the authentication method to be used for connections
    to the MySQL user account. The valid values are `mysql_native_password`
    or `caching_sha2_password`. If excluded when creating a new user, the
    default for the version of MySQL in use will be used. As of MySQL 8.0, the
    default is `caching_sha2_password`.

    + `mysql_native_password`
    + `caching_sha2_password`


