+ `description` (string, optional) - An optional free-form text field to describe an image.
+ `distribution` (enum[string], optional) - The name of a custom image's distribution. Currently, the valid values are  `Arch Linux`, `CentOS`, `CoreOS`, `Debian`, `Fedora`, `Fedora Atomic`,  `FreeBSD`, `Gentoo`, `openSUSE`, `RancherOS`, `Rocky Linux`, `Ubuntu`, and `Unknown`.  Any other value will be accepted but ignored, and `Unknown` will be used in its place.
    + `Arch Linux`
    + `CentOS`
    + `CoreOS`
    + `Debian`
    + `Fedora`
    + `Fedora Atomic`
    + `FreeBSD`
    + `Gentoo`
    + `openSUSE`
    + `RancherOS`
    + `Rocky Linux`
    + `Ubuntu`
    + `Unknown`
+ `name`: `Nifty New Snapshot` (string, required) - The display name that has been given to an image.  This is what is shown in the control panel and is generally a descriptive title for the image in question.
+ `region` (enum[string], required) - The slug identifier for the region where the resource will initially be  available.
    + `ams1`
    + `ams2`
    + `ams3`
    + `blr1`
    + `fra1`
    + `lon1`
    + `nyc1`
