## KubernetesCluster (object)


### Properties
+ `auto_upgrade`: `true` (boolean, optional) - A boolean value indicating whether the cluster will be automatically upgraded to new patch releases during its maintenance window.
+ `cluster_subnet`: `10.244.0.0/16` (string, optional) - The range of IP addresses in the overlay network of the Kubernetes cluster in CIDR notation.
+ `created_at`: `2018-11-15T16:00:11Z` (string, optional) - A time value given in ISO8601 combined date and time format that represents when the Kubernetes cluster was created.
+ `endpoint`: `https://bd5f5959-5e1e-4205-a714-a914373942af.k8s.ondigitalocean.com` (string, optional) - The base URL of the API server on the Kubernetes master node.
+ `ha`: `true` (boolean, optional) - A boolean value indicating whether the control plane is run in a highly available configuration in the cluster. Highly available control planes incur less downtime. The property cannot be disabled.
+ `id`: `bd5f5959-5e1e-4205-a714-a914373942af` (string, optional) - A unique ID that can be used to identify and reference a Kubernetes cluster.
+ `ipv4`: `68.183.121.157` (string, optional) - The public IPv4 address of the Kubernetes master node. This will not be set if high availability is configured on the cluster (v1.21+)
+ `maintenance_policy` (MaintenancePolicy, optional, nullable) - An object specifying the maintenance window policy for the Kubernetes cluster.
+ `name`: `prod-cluster-01` (string, required) - A human-readable name for a Kubernetes cluster.
+ `node_pools` (array[NodePool], required) - An object specifying the details of the worker nodes available to the Kubernetes cluster.
+ `region`: `nyc1` (string, required) - The slug identifier for the region where the Kubernetes cluster is located.
+ `registry_enabled`: `true` (boolean, optional) - A read-only boolean value indicating if a container registry is integrated with the cluster.
+ `service_subnet`: `10.245.0.0/16` (string, optional) - The range of assignable IP addresses for services running in the Kubernetes cluster in CIDR notation.
+ `status` (Status11, optional) - An object containing a `state` attribute whose value is set to a string indicating the current status of the cluster.
+ `surge_upgrade`: `true` (boolean, optional) - A boolean value indicating whether surge upgrade is enabled/disabled for the cluster. Surge upgrade makes cluster upgrades fast and reliable by bringing up new nodes before destroying the outdated nodes.
+ `tags`: `["k8s","k8s:bd5f5959-5e1e-4205-a714-a914373942af","production","web-team"]` (array[string], optional) - An array of tags applied to the Kubernetes cluster. All clusters are automatically tagged `k8s` and `k8s:$K8S_CLUSTER_ID`.
+ `updated_at`: `2018-11-15T16:00:11Z` (string, optional) - A time value given in ISO8601 combined date and time format that represents when the Kubernetes cluster was last updated.
+ `version`: `1.18.6-do.0` (string, required) - The slug identifier for the version of Kubernetes used for the cluster. If set to a minor version (e.g. "1.14"), the latest version within it will be used (e.g. "1.14.6-do.1"); if set to "latest", the latest published version will be used. See the `/v2/kubernetes/options` endpoint to find all currently available versions.
+ `vpc_uuid`: `c33931f2-a26a-4e61-b85c-4e95a2ec431b` (string, optional) - A string specifying the UUID of the VPC to which the Kubernetes cluster is assigned.


## MaintenancePolicy (object)
An object specifying the maintenance window policy for the Kubernetes cluster.

### Properties
+ `day` (enum[string], optional) - The day of the maintenance window policy. May be one of `monday` through `sunday`, or `any` to indicate an arbitrary week day.
    + `any`
    + `monday`
    + `tuesday`
    + `wednesday`
    + `thursday`
    + `friday`
    + `saturday`
    + `sunday`
+ `duration`: `4h0m0s` (string, optional) - The duration of the maintenance window policy in human-readable format.
+ `start_time`: `12:00` (string, optional) - The start time in UTC of the maintenance window policy in 24-hour clock format / HH:MM notation (e.g., `15:00`).


## NodePool (object)


### Properties
+ `size`: `s-1vcpu-2gb` (string, required) - The slug identifier for the type of Droplet used as workers in the node pool.
+ `auto_scale`: `true` (boolean, optional) - A boolean value indicating whether auto-scaling is enabled for this node pool.
+ `count`: `3` (number, required) - The number of Droplet instances in the node pool.
+ `id`: `cdda885e-7663-40c8-bc74-3a036c66545d` (string, optional) - A unique ID that can be used to identify and reference a specific node pool.
+ `labels` (object, optional, nullable) - An object containing a set of Kubernetes labels. The keys and are values are both user-defined.
+ `max_nodes`: `6` (number, optional) - The maximum number of nodes that this node pool can be auto-scaled to. The value will be `0` if `auto_scale` is set to `false`.
+ `min_nodes`: `3` (number, optional) - The minimum number of nodes that this node pool can be auto-scaled to. The value will be `0` if `auto_scale` is set to `false`.
+ `name`: `frontend-pool` (string, required) - A human-readable name for the node pool.
+ `nodes` (array[Node], optional) - An object specifying the details of a specific worker node in a node pool.
+ `tags`: `["k8s","k8s:bd5f5959-5e1e-4205-a714-a914373942af","k8s-worker","production","web-team"]` (array[string], optional) - An array containing the tags applied to the node pool. All node pools are automatically tagged `k8s`, `k8s-worker`, and `k8s:$K8S_CLUSTER_ID`.
+ `taints` (array[Taint], optional) - An array of taints to apply to all nodes in a pool. Taints will automatically be applied to all existing nodes and any subsequent nodes added to the pool. When a taint is removed, it is removed from all nodes in the pool.


